stories.title: Ponting and Vettori endorse annual series
stories.subTitle: Chappell-Hadlee Trophy, 2005-06
stories.summary: Ricky Ponting and Daniel Vettori believe the Chappell-Hadlee Trophy has the potential to become cricket's equivalent of rugby's Bledisloe Cup

stories.title: Katich battles to seal opening berth
stories.subTitle: Chappell-Hadlee Series
stories.summary: Simon Katich has vowed to find greater consistency in an effort to hold his place at the top of Australia's one-day side

stories.title: 'Anxious' Kiwis not scared of Lee
stories.subTitle: Chappell-Hadlee Series, 2005-06
stories.summary: Brendon McCullum has denied New Zealand's batsmen are scared of Brett Lee's pace but says they are definitely "anxious"

stories.title: NZ tightens crowd control to protect Australian cricketers
stories.subTitle: Chappell-Hadlee Trophy 2005-06
stories.summary: New Zealand cricket authorities have taken the unprecedented move of placing a buffer between players and fans for the remaining matches

stories.title: Australia v New Zealand, 1st ODI, Auckland
stories.subTitle: December 3, 2005

stories.title: Lee roars in to lead New Zealand demolition
stories.subTitle: New Zealand v Australia, Chappell-Hadlee Series, 1st ODI, Auckland
stories.summary: Brett Lee stepped up in the absence of Glenn McGrath and received impressive support from Nathan Bracken and Stuart Clark as New Zealand were shot out for 105 in only 27.4 overs

stories.title: No sledging against Aussies, says Mills
stories.subTitle: Chappell-Hadlee Trophy 2005-06
stories.summary: Kyle Mills, the New Zealand fast bowler, says that there shall be no premeditated sledging against Australia in the forthcoming Chappell-Hadlee Trophy starting on December 3
